### ============================================================
### MILESTONE MODULE — API LIFECYCLE TESTS
### File: backend/api-tests/milestone.http
### ============================================================
### HOW TO USE:
### 1. Install REST Client extension in VS Code
### 2. Run: npm run dev
### 3. Run Block 0 first to get your seed IDs
### 4. Paste IDs into @variables below
### 5. Send each request top to bottom
### ============================================================


### ============================================================
### BLOCK 0 — GET SEED IDs
### ============================================================


### 0.1 — Get all projects (copy a project ID)
GET http://localhost:3001/api/v1/projects
Content-Type: application/json

###

### ✏️ PASTE your project ID here after running 0.1
@projectId = ed8f395b-c3f8-444f-80e8-8244911a97f4


### ============================================================
### BLOCK 1 — CREATE
### ============================================================


### 1.1 — ✅ Create milestone (expect 201)
# @name milestone
POST http://localhost:3001/api/v1/projects/{{projectId}}/milestones
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Structural Assessment Complete",
  "due_date": "2026-12-04"
}

###

### ✏️ PASTE milestone ID here after running 1.1
@milestoneId = 511419a-4db1-45b8-bdec-764e6b25a073

### 1.2 — ❌ NEGATIVE: name too short — under 2 chars (expect 400)
POST http://localhost:3001/api/v1/projects/{{projectId}}/milestones
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "A",
  "due_date": "2026-06-30"
}

###

### 1.3 — ❌ NEGATIVE: due_date wrong format (expect 400)
POST http://localhost:3001/api/v1/projects/{{projectId}}/milestones
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Format Error Milestone",
  "due_date": "30-06-2026"
}

###

### 1.4 — ❌ NEGATIVE: due_date before project start_date (expect 400)
POST http://localhost:3001/api/v1/projects/{{projectId}}/milestones
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Too Early Milestone",
  "due_date": "2000-01-01"
}

###

### 1.5 — ❌ NEGATIVE: due_date after project end_date (expect 400)
POST http://localhost:3001/api/v1/projects/{{projectId}}/milestones
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Too Late Milestone",
  "due_date": "2099-12-31"
}

###

### 1.6 — ❌ NEGATIVE: missing name field (expect 400)
POST http://localhost:3001/api/v1/projects/{{projectId}}/milestones
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "due_date": "2026-06-30"
}

###

### 1.7 — ❌ NEGATIVE: missing due_date field (expect 400)
POST http://localhost:3001/api/v1/projects/{{projectId}}/milestones
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Missing Date Milestone"
}

###

### 1.8 — ❌ NEGATIVE: project does not exist (expect 404)
POST http://localhost:3001/api/v1/projects/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000/milestones
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Ghost Project Milestone",
  "due_date": "2026-06-30"
}

###


### ============================================================
### BLOCK 2 — READ
### ============================================================


### 2.1 — ✅ Get milestone by ID (expect 200)
GET http://localhost:3001/api/v1/milestones/{{milestoneId}}
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 2.2 — ✅ List all milestones for the project (expect 200, array)

GET http://localhost:3001/api/v1/projects/{{projectId}}/milestones
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 2.3 — ❌ NEGATIVE: milestone ID does not exist (expect 404)
GET http://localhost:3001/api/v1/milestones/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 2.4 — ❌ NEGATIVE: project ID does not exist (expect 404)
GET http://localhost:3001/api/v1/projects/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000/milestones
Content-Type: application/json

###


### ============================================================
### BLOCK 3 — UPDATE
### ============================================================


### 3.1 — ✅ Update milestone name (expect 200)
PUT http://localhost:3001/api/v1/milestones/{{milestoneId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Structural Assessment Complete - Revised"
}

###

### 3.2 — ✅ Update due_date only (expect 200)
PUT http://localhost:3001/api/v1/milestones/{{milestoneId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "due_date": "2026-07-15"
}

###

### 3.3 — ✅ Update both name and due_date (expect 200)
PUT http://localhost:3001/api/v1/milestones/{{milestoneId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Foundation Sign-Off",
  "due_date": "2026-07-01"
}

###

### 3.4 — ❌ NEGATIVE: empty body — no fields provided (expect 400)
PUT http://localhost:3001/api/v1/milestones/{{milestoneId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{}

###

### 3.5 — ❌ NEGATIVE: name too short (expect 400)
PUT http://localhost:3001/api/v1/milestones/{{milestoneId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "X"
}

###

### 3.6 — ❌ NEGATIVE: wrong date format (expect 400)
PUT http://localhost:3001/api/v1/milestones/{{milestoneId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "due_date": "July 15 2026"
}

###

### 3.7 — ❌ NEGATIVE: milestone does not exist (expect 404)
PUT http://localhost:3001/api/v1/milestones/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Ghost Update"
}

###


### ============================================================
### BLOCK 4 — COMPLETE (one-way door)
### ============================================================


### 4.1 — ✅ Mark milestone as complete (expect 200, is_completed: true)
PATCH http://localhost:3001/api/v1/milestones/{{milestoneId}}/complete
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 4.2 — ✅ Verify is_completed is now true (expect 200)
GET http://localhost:3001/api/v1/milestones/{{milestoneId}}
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 4.3 — ❌ NEGATIVE: complete an already-completed milestone (expect 400)
PATCH http://localhost:3001/api/v1/milestones/{{milestoneId}}/complete
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 4.4 — ❌ NEGATIVE: complete a milestone that does not exist (expect 404)
PATCH http://localhost:3001/api/v1/milestones/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000/complete
Content-Type: application/json

###


### ============================================================
### BLOCK 5 — DELETE
### ============================================================


### 5.1 — ✅ Create a disposable milestone to delete (expect 201)
# @name disposableMilestone
POST http://localhost:3001/api/v1/projects/{{projectId}}/milestones
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "To Be Deleted",
  "due_date": "2026-08-01"
}

###

### ✏️ PASTE disposable milestone ID here after running 5.1
@disposableMilestoneId = PASTE_DISPOSABLE_MILESTONE_UUID_HERE

### 5.2 — ✅ Delete the disposable milestone (expect 204 — empty body)
DELETE http://localhost:3001/api/v1/milestones/{{disposableMilestoneId}}
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 5.3 — ❌ NEGATIVE: Get the deleted milestone (expect 404)
GET http://localhost:3001/api/v1/milestones/{{disposableMilestoneId}}
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 5.4 — ❌ NEGATIVE: Delete a milestone that does not exist (expect 404)
DELETE http://localhost:3001/api/v1/milestones/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
Content-Type: application/json

###


